      "content": "that makes sense. so basically concrete handles the weight pushing down on it, but the steel handles the pulling/stretching forces? can you explain a bit more about what actually happens inside the material when a load is applied—like, how do those internal forces distribute between the two so the whole thing doesn't just snap?",
